calcDiffCollAmountForRatio(uint256,uint2.details: calc how much collateral amount has to be added to have a ratio

params._borrowedAskAmount: loan borrowed ask amount in stable coins
params._ratio: ratio to reach, percentage with no decimals (180 means 180%)

returns.collDiff: collateral amount to add or to subtract to reach that ratio

calcMinCollateralAmount(uint256,uint256).details: get the amount of collateral needed to have stable coin amount (no fees)

params._askAmount: amount in stable coin the borrower would like to receive

returns._0: amount of collateral the borrower needs to send

calcMinCollateralWithFeesAmount(uint256,.details: get the amount of collateral needed to have stable coin amount, with fees

params._askAmount: amount in stable coin the borrower would like to receive

returns._0: amount of collateral the borrower needs to send

calcRatioAddingCollateral(uint256,uint25.details: calc a new ratio if collateral amount has added to contract balance

returns.ratio: new collateral ratio, percentage with no decimals

createNewEthLoan(uint256,uint256,uint256.details: create a new loan with eth as collateraland set the address in the mapping

params._borrowedAskAmount: amount in stable coin the borrower would like to receive
params._pairId: number of the pair interested in the loan contract
params._rpbRate: RPB rate the borrower will pay

createNewTokenLoan(uint256,uint256,uint2.details: create a new loan and set the address in the mapping

params._borrowedAskAmount: amount in stable coin the borrower would like to receive
params._pairId: number of the pair interested in the loan contract
params._rpbRate: RPB rate the borrower will pay

getActualCollateralRatio(uint256,address.details: get the collateral ratio of the loan (subtracting the accrued interests)

params._borrowedAskAmount: loan borrowed ask amount in stable coins

getDeployedLoan(uint256).details: get a single loan address deployed by the factory
